According to Genius:
While on the surface, it simply seems as if he’s expressing his distaste for this day of the week, this line bears an interesting double-entendre. Sundays are days in which most Christians go to Church. Christians go to Church in an effort to learn more about their God and essentially ‘kill’ the sinful parts of themselves in an effort to more efficiently serve their Lord. On a technical note, the rhyme scheme beginning with this verse and ending with ‘suicide days’ is a great example of how Tyler frequently makes use of compound syllables and heavy assonance. Despite Tyler Joseph’s seemingly low confidence in his rapping abilities, the technicalities shown here displays some talent: I-I-I I’ve got a migraine And my pain will range from up, down, and sideways Thank God it’s Friday cause Fridays will always be better than Sundays Cause Sundays are my suicide days
